Package frogger.models.actors

Class WetTurtle

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
frogger.models.actors.Actor
frogger.models.actors.Rideable
frogger.models.actors.WetTurtle
All Implemented Interfaces:
IRideable, ISinkable, javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class WetTurtle
extends Rideable
implements ISinkable

The class WetTurtle is a Rideable that can be ridden by Player when intersected.

WetTurtles are added into Level classes using World.add(Actor) to create a visible instance of a WetTurtle in the level.

  • Method Details

    • act

      public void act​(long now)

      Method called by AnimationTimer in World.createTimer() to cause WetTurtle to act every game frame.

      Moves the WetTurtle based on speed every frame and ensures the WetTurtle objects will be in game bounds. WetTurtle animation is also animated here.

      WetTurtle state of whether it is sunk is also set here.

      Specified by:
      act in interface IRideable
      Overrides:
      act in class Rideable
      Parameters:
      now - The timestamp of the current frame given in nanoseconds.
